{
  // TEST CASE 18: Multi-Constellation Candidate — Single Simulation
  //
  // Background constellation: 100 satellites across 25 altitude bands (300–2500 km).
  //   Each band has a distinct inclination; bands are at least 50 km apart so
  //   inter-band collisions are impossible.  Inclinations span 0°–165° for dense
  //   visual crisscrossing across the globe.
  //   Original 6 bands: Blue i=0° / Cyan i=90° / Green i=45° / Orange i=60° / Purple i=120° / Magenta i=150°
  //   19 additional bands at 300/350/450/600/650/750/850/900/950/1100/1150/1300/1400/1500/1600/1800/2000/2200/2500 km.
  //
  // 700 km band (r=7,071,000 m, v=7,508 m/s):
  //   Target (Red):     ( 7,071,000,  0, 0) m · v=(0, +7508, 0) m/s · CCW
  //   Candidate (Yellow): (-7,071,000, 0, 0) m · v=(0, +7508, 0) m/s · CW
  //
  // The candidate is at the same altitude as the target but on a counter-orbit
  // (clockwise). Both head toward (0, +7,071,000, 0). Straight-line closing
  // distance d(t) = 2r·|cos(ωt)| → passes through 20,000 m (combined radius)
  // at t ≈ 1479 steps.  Collision should be reported at step ~1479.
  //
  // Radius 10,000 m each so combined zone (20 km) > per-step closing (15,016 m).

  "name": "Multi-constellation: candidate in collision orbit (single sim)",
  "outerSetup": "SimulationRunSetup",
  "innerSetup": "SatelliteSetup",
  "description": "100 background satellites across 25 altitude bands (300–2500 km), each band in a distinct orbital plane with inclinations spanning 0°–165° for dense crisscrossing orbits. A single target satellite (Red) at 700 km orbits equatorially CCW. The candidate (Yellow) is placed at 700 km on a counter-orbit (CW): the worst possible starting position. Closing speed ~15,016 m/s, combined collision zone 20,000 m. Collision expected at step ~1479.",
  "headerLines": [
    "TEST CASE 18: Multi-Constellation Candidate (single simulation)",
    "Background: 100 sats across 25 bands (300–2500 km), inclinations 0°–165°",
